# pygeoglim

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/pygeoglim.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/pygeoglim)
[![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/pygeoglim.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/pygeoglim/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**`pygeoglim`** is a Python package for extracting geology attributes‚Äîspecifically lithological and hydrogeological properties‚Äîfrom **GLiM** and **GLHYMPS** datasets for any region or watershed in CONUS region. It is built for use in hydrological modeling, large-sample hydrology, and Earth system research.

